1>selective
2>iterative 
3>transfer


1> if(boolean){
	
   }else{
	
   }

   : curly barces and else part is optional
   : only one statement we can write without curly braces after if

2> switch(byte,short, char , int(1.4) , Byte , short , char , Ineteger(1.5) , enum){
    case 1 : action ; break;
    case 2: action ; break;
    default : action;
    }

    : independent statement not allowed
    : case lable should be compile time constant int y =10 ; case y(invalid) if final 
      it is valid
    : switch argument can be expression and class label should be constant expression
    : case label should be with in  switch argument range
    : duplicate case labels are not allowed




1> while(boolean){
       // statements
     }

     : if we dont know no of iteration

2> do{
      int x = 10 ; should not declarative without curly braces
     }while(boolean){

     }

     : if we want to execute loop body at least once without condition chacking

3>for loop : innitialization  : int a=0,b=0
                                : can take any java statement including sop
                                : execute only once

             : condition checking : boolean expression allowed
                                  : not mendatary if not declared compiler will take 
                                    true;
             : increment decrement : any valid java statement allowed including sop
                                   : optional

             : all three part are optional
             : curly braces are optional without it we can use only one non declrative
               statement



4> for each : itarate through collection and array
			int[][] a;
			for(int[] x : a){
			 for (int[] y : x)
			}







1> break : inside switch : to break fall through
         : inside loop :  while(true){
         					if(true){
         					break;
         					}
         				  } 
         : inside labeled block : l1 : {
         								 if(x>:11);
         								 break;

         								}



2> continue : skip current iteration and continue next iteration
             : can be used in loop after condition
              if(true) continue ; 







